# Deployment Commands - Sample

Replace the following variables with your own values:

- `${GCP_PROJECT_ID}` - Your Google Cloud Project ID
- `${GCP_REGION}` - Your preferred region (e.g., us-central1)
- `${ARTIFACT_REPO_NAME}` - Your Artifact Registry repository name
- `${SERVICE_NAME}` - Your Cloud Run service name

## 1. Create Artifact Registry Repository

```bash
gcloud artifacts repositories create ${ARTIFACT_REPO_NAME} \
  --repository-format docker \
  --project ${GCP_PROJECT_ID} \
  --location ${GCP_REGION}

# 2. Build and push Docker image
  gcloud builds submit \
  --config=cloudbuild.yaml \
  --project ${GCP_PROJECT_ID}

# 3 Deploy to Cloud Run
gcloud run services replace service.yaml \
  --region ${GCP_REGION} \
  --project ${GCP_PROJECT_ID}

#4. Set IAM Policy (Optional - for public access)

gcloud run services set-iam-policy ${SERVICE_NAME} \
  gcr-service-policy.yaml \
  --region ${GCP_REGION} \
  --project ${GCP_PROJECT_ID}


  